Package: bigedit
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}, fuse3
Recommends: inotify-tools
Description: Streaming TUI editor for very large files
 BigEdit is a terminal-based text editor designed to handle multi-gigabyte
 files efficiently. It uses streaming I/O and patch-based editing to avoid
 loading entire files into memory.
 .
 Features:
  - Edit files larger than RAM
  - Nano-like keybindings
  - FUSE virtual file system for viewing patched content
  - Journal-based saves for instant writes
  - Systemd service for auto-mounting patched views on boot
